Senate Resolution 265
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life of Mr. Samuel Micah Moon and dedicating an interchange in his memory;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mr. Samuel Micah Moon was born in Austell, Georgia, on March 30, 2007, the
4 beloved son of Beverly La Fleur and Shendi Moon; and
5 WHEREAS, Mr. Moon was a STEM student at Lithia Springs High School, with an expected
6 graduation date of 2025; and
7 WHEREAS, he had a passion for music and enjoyed spending time with his friends and
8 family, hiking, and fishing; and
9 WHEREAS, Mr. Moon's life was tragically cut short on March 4, 2023, when he was one
10 of ten children shot at a sweet 16 birthday party in Douglas County; and
11 WHEREAS, known for his amazing sense of humor and infectious smile, Mr. Moon will
12 long be remembered for his love of family and friendship, and this loyal son and friend will
13 be missed by all who had the great fortune of knowing him; and
